'''Buzitka''' ({{lang-hu|Bozita}}) is a village and municipality in the [[Lučenec District]] in the [[Banská Bystrica Region]] of [[Slovakia]].

==History==
In [[history|historical records]], the village was first mentioned in 1350 (''Bozyta'') when it belonged to Fil'akovo. From 1554 to 1595 it was occupied by the [[Ottoman Empire]]. In 1625, when it was ruled by the family Serényi, it paid tributes to Turks.
